metadata.name: Coloring With Lines #324
metadata.description:
This project started as a way to teach myself more about classes in p5.js by trying to code the "Chaos Game" method of plotting a Serpinski Triangle

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kbKtFN71Lfs

Once figured out, I expanded the method to other shapes to see if different types of fractals might form. They did not, but the result was a series of points that could be connected with thin lines to draw shapes without using the native functions of p5. After working on colors it seemed like a nice enough project to release for free to everyone. Thank you all for your interest and support, hope you get a cool one!

metadata.name: Euphonic #840
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: White flags #100
metadata.description:
All I can do for the moment, is give the world some paint-bombs and color explosions. Focus on things you like and love, don't let the hate consume you.


mouse-click: 
- screen scaled image
- full image 3000x3000

The scaled image will reset after some time, with a new drawing
I like it, when you make a work, that will refresh after sometime,
chill out, and see it go.

Tech - Vanilla java-script; a custom build 'soft' 3D-engine.
I can do more things if I can control the (3D) drawing, the color of every pixel.
Also added a z-buffer to the  line-drawing routine this time.
More information in the source-code.

metadata.name: Festival #52
metadata.description:
In the meta color space of the digital light spectrum, red, green, and blue lived peacefully.

But then, a being from beyond (BFB) stirred up the colors and started to apply functions and functions upon functions. Red, green, and blue grew tired and weary of the manipulation and broke up into weird random structures.

The BFB was disheartened, but realising the colors pains, searched for more simple harmonies between the colors, and applied endless variations to tease vibrancy into the life of the colors. The colors rewarded the BFB with Festival, their dance of joy. 

Made with p5js, a bit of math and plenty of experimentation. Gold is rare, super high or low density is rare.
